{
  "text": "The forces that act on the cod-end are the twine tensions and the hydrodynamic forces. As shown by O'Neill and O'Donoghue [CITATION_1] , the hydrodynamic forces that act on the unblocked netting are negligible in comparison with the pressure forces acting on the netting where the catch blocks the meshes. Consequently, it is only necessary to consider the twine tensions and the pressure forces that act in the region of the catch.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "119575131"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "119575131": {
      "title": "The fluid dynamic loading on catch and the geometry of trawl cod-ends",
      "abstract": "A qualitative description of the hydrodynamic forces that act on the catch in the cod\u2013end of a trawl net is presented. Based on this description, theoretical predictions of the cod\u2013end geometry are obtained numerically from the governing differential equations. These are compared with the experimental results of a series of wind tunnel trials and are shown to be in good agreement."
    }
  }
}